(set-info :smt-lib-version 2.6)
(set-logic QF_SLIA)
(set-info :source |
Generated by: Georgiy Belyanin, Mikhail Starchak
Generated on: 2026-02-19
Application: Evaluate string solvers on problems featuring combinations of length constraints and string-to-integer conversions
Target solver: CVC5, Z3-Noodler
Time limit: 60.0
Generated benchmarks featuring regular constraints, linear integer constraints over
string lengths, integers converted from strings and concatenation.
Each benchmark contains from 2 to 4 string variables, which occur in the scope of
str.len and str.to_int functions. The assertions are composed of
— a regular constraint over each variable;
— 1, 2, or 3 linear constraints over string lengths and variables converted to integers;
— one word equation with constants over decimal digits (e.g. "20"++x = z++y+"26").
The benchmarks are split into three categories:
— "random", with integer coefficients ranging from -10 to 10 and constants from -100 to 100;
— "long", with at least one assertion requiring the length of a variable to be more than 1000;
— "z3-hard", which are unsolvable by Z3 in 10s (on a single Intel Core i7-6700 CPU core @ 3.40GHz with 8GB of DDR5 RAM).
|)
